# Styling & UI Guidelines

## Design System
- Uses Tailwind CSS v4 with custom design tokens
- Shadcn/ui components with "new-york" style
- Custom color palette with OKLCH color space
- Dark mode support with CSS custom properties

## Component Library
- All UI components in `components/ui/`
- Use Radix UI primitives as base
- Implement proper accessibility features
- Follow compound component patterns

## Styling Patterns
```typescript
// Use cn utility for conditional classes
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"

<div className={cn("base-classes", conditionalClass, className)} />

// Use CSS custom properties for theming
<div style={{ "--custom-property": value }} />

// Use Tailwind responsive prefixes
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3" />
```

## Color System
- Primary: Purple/violet theme
- Semantic colors: success, warning, error, info
- Muted colors for secondary content
- Proper contrast ratios for accessibility

## Typography
- Custom letter-spacing: `--tracking-normal`
- Typography component with variants
- Proper heading hierarchy
- Responsive text sizing

## Layout Components
- Container component for consistent spacing
- Responsive grid systems
- Proper spacing scale
- Mobile-first responsive design

## Animation
- CSS custom properties for animations
- Fade in/out transitions
- Shine effects for special elements
- Smooth scrolling and interactions

## Accessibility
- Proper ARIA labels and roles
- Keyboard navigation support
- Focus management
- Screen reader compatibility